    Login Email

    This is the email that is sent to the user when they are attempting to log in.
    It is important to note that we do NOT have access to our typical CSS classes here,
    so everything must be done inline.
#}
<h1>Login to Tapalava</h1>
<p>
    Your link to login is below. If you were not trying to login, just ignore
    this email.
</p>
<a
    href="{{ url('login-authorize', {"code": code, "email": email}) }}"
    style="
        background-color: #326598;
        color: #fff;
        border-radius: 2px;
        padding: 0 16px;
        line-height: 36px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        font-size: 14px;
        display: inline-block;
        text-decoration: none;
        box-shadow: 0 2px 2px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, .14), 0 3px 1px -2px rgba(0, 0, 0, .2), 0 1px 5px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, .12);
        font-family: Lato, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    "
